ORGANIZER;CN="Molina, Javier (NCMI, Clayton)":mailto:Javier.Molina@csiro.au
DESCRIPTION:                              \nWhat to expect\nOfficially laun
 ched in February 2026\, the Flemish Biodiversity Portal (VBP) has become t
 he definitive central hub for biodiversity data in Flanders\, Belgium. Dev
 eloped by the INBO\, the portal successfully adapts the Atlas of Living Au
 stralia (ALA) open-source framework to provide researchers\, policymakers\
 , and the public with real-time access to regional natural heritage.\n\nTh
 e portal currently integrates over 30 million occurrence records from more
  than 300 diverse datasets\, including museum collections\, scientific mon
 itoring networks\, and citizen science. By harmonizing these sources throu
 gh Darwin Core standards\, the VBP enables precise tracking of species dis
 tributions\, invasive species trends\, and habitat health within the speci
 fic Flemish landscape.\n\nFor the Living Atlases Community\, the VBP stand
 s as a successful implementation of a "Living Atlas" instance in a high-de
 nsity\, Flemish context. It provides critical infrastructure for meeting E
 uropean Nature Restoration targets and regional policy needs. While the po
 rtal is now operational\, ongoing development focuses on enhancing data fl
 ows—particularly the real-time integration of broad citizen science data
 —and refining secure access for sensitive species. The VBP demonstrates 
 how localized data mobilization can drive evidence-based conservation acro
 ss borders.\n\nThis presentation offers a deep dive into the VBP\, illustr
 ating how the original ALA codebase was adapted for a Flemish audience and
  its reception within the local community. We will specifically address th
 e hurdles overcome during implementation\, including the technical challen
 ges of localizing a complex Australian architecture for a Dutch-speaking p
 ublic.\n\n\n\nThis event will be recorded and the recording made available
  through the Living Atlases slack channel in the week after the event.\n\n
 Time and date\nWednesday 22 April 2026 5-6pm AEST (7-8am UTC)\nSee it in y
 our local time zone<https://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?
 msg=Living+Atlases+Information+Session+-+Deep+dive+into+the+Flemish+Biodiv
 ersity+Portal&iso=20260422T17&p1=152&ah=1>.\n\nHow to join\nThis is an onl
 ine event that will be broadcast using MS Teams\, follow the links below t
 o join.\nhttps://teams.microsoft.com/meet/45445242223484?p=4PkBVfIpcknp7kE
 lvJ\nMeeting ID: 454 452 422 234 84\nPasscode: 9PJ9so6R\n\n\nFurther infor
 mation\nThis event will be recorded and the recording made available throu
 gh the Living Atlases slack channel<https://ala.us14.list-manage.com/track
 /click?u=b238aea31bbd4bd103ff7368c&id=4252e0d32e&e=e24f40f4fd> in the week
  after the event.\nIf you have any questions\, please reach out to support
 @ala.org.au<mailto:support@ala.org.au>\n\n\n______________________________
